  "title" => "List of Countries without Coronavirus case"
  "description" => """
    Are there Countries Without Coronavirus?\r\n
    EDIT - as of 17th AUGUST 2022 when North Korea announced its first case of COVID-19, there is only one country left on this list of countries without coronavirus; Turkmenistan. \r\n
    This blog has been constantly edited since February 2020 to keep up with countries that had no cases of COVID-19. Starting with 30 countries, there is now only one left, 3 years later into the pandemic.\r\n
    \r\n
    What a couple of years it has been... \r\n
    \r\n
    UPDATED: JANUARY 2022\r\n
    The spread of the coronavirus took us all by surprise, and the speed at which it has spread all over the world is alarming. So much so, that it is almost hard to believe that some countries still have no reported cases of the Coronavirus/COVID-19. \r\n
    \r\n
    Well, there are in fact countries without coronavirus! \r\n
    \r\n
    The UN officially recognises 193 countries. \r\n
    \r\n
    As of JANUARY 2023, only 1 country has not confirmed any cases of COVID-19. Many of these countries to get COVID last were Pacific Island countries in Oceania.
    """
]
